{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} '''Substrate''' is a term used in converting process such as [[printing]] or coating as a more general term to describe the base material onto which e.g. [[image]]s will be printed. Base materials include (though are not limited to): * plastic films or foils, * [[release liner]] * [[textile]]s, * [[fabrics]], * plastic containers * any variety of [[paper]] (lightweight, heavyweight, coated, uncoated, paperboard, cardboard, etc.), or * [[parchment]].
